        "description": "As per the [documentation of Time#now() method|https://github.com/apache/hadoop/blob/74411ce0ce7336c0f7bb5793939fdd64a5dcdef6/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/util/Time.java#L49-L57], it should not be used for calculating duration or interval to sleep. But the TGT renewer thread in UserGroupInformation object doesn't follow this recommendation,\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/apache/hadoop/blob/74411ce0ce7336c0f7bb5793939fdd64a5dcdef6/hadoop-common-project/hadoop-common/src/main/java/org/apache/hadoop/security/UserGroupInformation.java#L892-L899]\r\n\r\nThis should be fixed to use Time.monotonicNow() API instead.\r\n\r\nÂ ",
